sub_title: Assistant Professor at University of Amsterdam/ Senior Researcher at the International Migration Institute
summary:
Ladan Rahbari (PhD Mult.) is an assistant professor of sociology at the University of Amsterdam. Rahbari was the recipient of an FWO (Research Foundation Flanders) post-doctoral fellowship (2019-2022). She received a Ph.D. in Gender and Diversity (Studies) from UGent and VUB and a Ph.D. in Sociology from Mazandaran University (gelijkwaardig erkend in België als "Doctor in de Politieke en Sociale Wetenschappen"), a Master’s degree in Anthropology and a Bachelor’s degree in Italian Literature.

She is a member of the Young Academy Amsterdam (AYA, 2021-2026): https://amsterdamyoungacademy.nl/who_we_are/members/ladan-rahbari 

Rahbari lectures on race and migration, gender politics, digital media, and diversity. She has extensive teaching and research experience in several universities. 

She is currently affiliated with CRCG (UGent), RHEA (VUB), AR-CGS (UvA), and ACMES (UvA). Between September 2019 and September 2020, Rahbari was the editor-in-chief of the Journal of Diversity and Gender Studies (DiGeSt). She is currently a member of the editorial board at DiGeSt.
